questions.content:
The number of elements in the set $$\left\{ {A = \left( {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   0 &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right):a,b,d \in \{  - 1,0,1\} \,and\,{{(I - A)}^3} = I - {A^3}} \right\}$$, where I is 2 $$\times$$ 2 identity matrix, is :

questions.explanation:
$${(I - A)^3} = {I^3} - {A^3} - 3A(I - A) = I - {A^3}$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 3A(I - A) = 0$$ or $${A^2} = A$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \left[ {\matrix{
   {{a^2}} &amp; {ab + bd}  \cr 
   0 &amp; {{d^2}}  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   a &amp; b  \cr 
   0 &amp; d  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {a^2} = a,b(a + d - 1) = 0,{d^2} = d$$<br><br>If b $$\ne$$ 0, a + d = 1 $$\Rightarrow$$ 4 ways<br><br>If b = 0, a = 0, 1 &amp; d = 0, 1 $$\Rightarrow$$ 4 ways<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ Total 8 matrices
